
@startuml

' Entities involved in the system
class Cinema {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - town: string
}

class Theatre {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - capacity: int
    - cinema: Cinema
}

class Movie {
    - id: int
    - title: string
    - duration: int (minutes)
    - releaseDate: date
}

class Copy {
    - id: int
    - movie: Movie
    - cinema: Cinema
    - status: string (e.g., "available", "in use")
}

class Show {
    - id: int
    - startTime: datetime
    - endTime: datetime
    - theatre: Theatre
    - copy: Copy
    - publishedDate: date
    - isCancelled: boolean
}

class Seat {
    - id: int
    - row: int
    - number: int
    - theatre: Theatre
}

class Customer {
    - id: int
    - name: string
    - email: string
    - creditCard: CreditCard
}

class CreditCard {
    - id: int
    - number: string
    - expiryDate: date
    - customer: Customer
}

class Reservation {
    - id: int
    - show: Show
    - seat: Seat
    - customer: Customer
    - reservationTime: datetime
    - isCancelled: boolean
    - paymentProcessed: boolean
}

class Ticket {
    - id: int
    - show: Show
    - seat: Seat
    - customer: Customer (optional)
    - issuedAtEntrance: boolean
    - issueTime: datetime
}

class Offer {
    - id: int
    - reservation: Reservation
    - newShow: Show
    - newSeat: Seat
    - expiresAt: datetime
    - accepted: boolean
}

class FreeTicket {
    - id: int
    - reservation: Reservation
    - sentToCustomer: boolean
    - sendDate: date
}

class Display {
    - theatre: Theatre
    - availableSeats: int
    - show: Show
}

' Relationships
Cinema "1" -- "many" Theatre
Theatre "1" -- "many" Seat
Theatre "1" -- "many" Show
Show "1" -- "1" Copy
Copy "1" -- "1" Movie
Show "1" -- "many" Reservation
Reservation "1" -- "1" Seat
Reservation "1" -- "1" Customer
Customer "1" -- "1" CreditCard
Show "1" -- "many" Ticket
Ticket "0..1" -- "1" Customer
Offer "1" -- "1" Reservation
Offer "1" -- "1" NewShow
Offer "1" -- "1" NewSeat
FreeTicket "1" -- "1" Reservation
Display "1" -- "1" Theatre
Display "1" -- "1" Show

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Cinema**: Owns theatres and stores copies of movies.
- **Theatre**: Located within a cinema and has seats and shows.
- **Movie & Copy**: A copy is a physical instance of a movie used for showing in a specific cinema.
- **Show**: Represents a scheduled screening of a movie in a theatre using a copy.
- **Reservation**: Made online by customers before the 24-hour cancellation window.
- **CreditCard**: Used for online payments.
- **Ticket**: Assigned to a seat; can be from online reservation or at the entrance.
- **Offer**: Generated when a show is cancelled, offering an alternative seat/reservation.
- **FreeTicket**: Sent to customers if no alternatives are available after cancellation.
- **Display**: Shows available seats at the ticketing desk.

